      "content": "So if the mainstream view is that the \"suppression\" is just overstated, does that mean the concerns about it are basically just baseless? It feels like you're saying the economic costs are just political noise, but for people in those specific low-skilled groups who *are* actually losing money, isn't that a very real and documented economic reality regardless of the \"broader\" view?",
